Notation: <br>
<font color = 'green'>sage:</font color> 'What we enter into sage' (note, we do not enter the 'sage:' part) <br>
>>> <font color = 'blue'> 'The result that is returned by sage' </font color> <br>
<br>
To find the Null-space of a matrix, type <br>
<font color = 'green'>sage:</font color> A.right_kernel() <br>
>>> <font color = 'blue'> Vector space of degree 3 and dimension 1 over Rational Field <br>
Basis matrix: <br>
[ 1 -2  1] </font color> <br>
Where 'A' is the matrix you have previously defined (see 'How do I enter a matrix in sage' above) <br>
For more information see <br>
http://www.sagemath.org/doc/reference/modules/sage/modules/free_module_element.html